The article is a transcript of remarks made by Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas and President Donald Trump during their meeting in Bethlehem. President Abbas welcomed President Trump and expressed hope for a lasting and just peace between Palestine and Israel. He reiterated the Palestinian commitment to the two-state solution and called for an end to the Israeli occupation and settlements. President Abbas also highlighted the issue of Palestinian prisoners and called on the Israeli government to meet their demands. President Trump offered his condolences to the victims of the Manchester terrorist attack and expressed solidarity with the people of the United Kingdom. He emphasized the need to drive out terrorism and protect innocent lives. President Trump pledged to work towards achieving a peace agreement between Palestine and Israel and to unlock the potential of the Palestinian economy. He also mentioned his recent meeting with leaders of Muslim and Arab nations in Saudi Arabia and the importance of their partnership in combating terrorism. President Trump expressed hope that peace between Palestine and Israel would lead to peace throughout the Middle East.